---
layout: layouts/element.njk
title: "brand-mark"
description: "Inert custom element for brand/logo display. Use in headers, footers, and anywhere you need consistent brand representation."
elementName: brand-mark
category: custom
currentPath: /docs/elements/custom-elements/brand-mark/
permalink: /docs/elements/custom-elements/brand-mark/
---

{% set basicCode %}<brand-mark>
  <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" />
  Acme Inc
</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set sizesCode %}<brand-mark data-size="s">Small</brand-mark>

<brand-mark>Default</brand-mark>

<brand-mark data-size="l">Large</brand-mark>

<brand-mark data-size="xl">Extra Large</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set stackedCode %}<brand-mark data-stack>
  <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" />
  Acme Inc
</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set linkCode %}<a href="/">
  <brand-mark>
    <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" />
    Acme Inc
  </brand-mark>
</a>{% endset %}

{% set srcCode %}<brand-mark src="/logo.svg" alt="Acme Inc">
  Acme Inc
</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set wordmarkCode %}<brand-mark src="/logo.svg" wordmark>
  Acme Inc
</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set heightCode %}<brand-mark src="/logo.svg" wordmark height="40">
  Acme Inc
</brand-mark>{% endset %}

{% set headerCode %}<header>
  <nav>
    <a href="/">
      <brand-mark>
        <img src="/logo.svg" alt="" />
        Acme Inc
      </brand-mark>
    </a>
    <!-- Navigation items -->
  </nav>
</header>{% endset %}

<section>
    <h2>Overview</h2>
    <p>The <code>&lt;brand-mark&gt;</code> element provides a consistent way to display your brand name and logo. It handles typography, spacing, and link styling automatically.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Attributes</h2>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr>
          <th>Attribute</th>
          <th>Values</th>
          <th>Default</th>
          <th>Description</th>
        </tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>src</code></td>
          <td>URL</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Path to logo image (SVG preferred). JS enhancement injects an <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> element.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>alt</code></td>
          <td>string</td>
          <td>text content</td>
          <td>Alt text for the logo image. Defaults to the element's text content.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>wordmark</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Show text alongside the image logo. Without this, only the image is shown.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>height</code></td>
          <td>number (px)</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Explicit pixel height for the logo image.</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-size</code></td>
          <td><code>s</code>, <code>l</code>, <code>xl</code></td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Adjust brand mark size</td>
        </tr>
        <tr>
          <td><code>data-stack</code></td>
          <td>boolean</td>
          <td>-</td>
          <td>Stack logo and text vertically</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Basic Usage</h2>
    <p>Wrap your brand name in the element, optionally with a logo image. Use an empty <code>alt</code> on the image since the brand name provides the text alternative.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/brand-mark-basic.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/brand-mark"
      title="Brand mark"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Brand mark with logo">{{ basicCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Image Logo via <code>src</code></h2>
    <p>Use the <code>src</code> attribute to load a logo image. The JS enhancement injects an <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> element automatically. Without JS, the text content renders as a fallback — this is progressive enhancement.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Logo image (image only)">{{ srcCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>By default, only the image is shown. The text content becomes the <code>alt</code> text or <code>aria-label</code>.</p>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Image + Wordmark</h2>
    <p>Add the <code>wordmark</code> attribute to show the brand name text alongside the logo image.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Logo with wordmark">{{ wordmarkCode | escape }}</code-block>

    <p>Use <code>height</code> to control the image size explicitly. The CSS token <code>--brand-mark-height</code> can also be set by themes.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Custom height">{{ heightCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Sizes</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-size</code> to adjust the brand mark for different contexts.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/brand-mark-sizes.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/brand-mark/sizes"
      title="Brand mark sizes"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Brand mark sizes">{{ sizesCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Stacked Layout</h2>
    <p>Use <code>data-stack</code> for vertical logo and text arrangement. Useful for centered layouts like login pages or footers.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/brand-mark-stacked.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/brand-mark/stacked"
      title="Stacked brand mark"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Stacked brand mark">{{ stackedCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>As a Link</h2>
    <p>Wrap in an anchor to make the brand mark clickable. The element automatically removes link underlines and adjusts hover states.</p>

    <browser-window
      src="/docs/snippets/demos/brand-mark-link.html"
      url="https://vanilla-breeze.dev/brand-mark/link"
      title="Brand mark as link"
      shadow>
    </browser-window>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Brand mark as link">{{ linkCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>In a Header</h2>
    <p>Common usage in site headers with navigation.</p>

    <code-block language="html" show-lines label="Brand mark in header">{{ headerCode | escape }}</code-block>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Accessibility</h2>
    <ul>
      <li>When using the <code>src</code> attribute without <code>wordmark</code>, the text content is used as <code>aria-label</code> or image <code>alt</code></li>
      <li>When using <code>wordmark</code>, the image gets <code>alt=""</code> (decorative) since the visible text provides the label</li>
      <li>When manually adding an <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> child, set <code>alt=""</code> since the brand name text provides the text alternative</li>
      <li>When wrapped in a link, the brand name serves as the link text</li>
      <li>Ensure sufficient color contrast between brand text and background</li>
      <li>Focus states are handled automatically when wrapped in a link</li>
      <li>Without JS, the <code>src</code> attribute has no effect — text content always provides a readable fallback</li>
    </ul>
  </section>

  <section>
    <h2>Content Model</h2>

    <h3>Permitted Content</h3>
    <ul>
      <li>Text (brand name)</li>
      <li>Optional <code>&lt;img&gt;</code> or <code>&lt;svg&gt;</code> (logo)</li>
    </ul>

    <h3>Permitted Parents</h3>
    <p>Any flow content. Commonly placed inside <code>&lt;a&gt;</code>, <code>&lt;header&gt;</code>, or <code>&lt;nav&gt;</code>.</p>

    <h3>CSS Tokens</h3>
    <table class="props-table">
      <thead>
        <tr><th>Token</th><th>Default</th><th>Description</th></tr>
      </thead>
      <tbody>
        <tr>
          <td><code>--brand-mark-height</code></td>
          <td><code>2rem</code></td>
          <td>Height of the logo image (set by themes)</td>
        </tr>
      </tbody>
    </table>
  </section>

